      I listen to music while eating.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
This sentence pattern can also be used to say that two actions take place over a period of time.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{work}}:hatara}}ki@EM{{nagara}}@KJ{{day^book^word}}wo@FG{{@KJ{{exertion^strong}}:benkyou}}shiteimasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I am working and studying Japanese.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{nagara}} can be used between two clauses to emphasise that they are opposite in meaning.
See <a href="grammar-nagara-although.html">here</a> for more details.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
